Detailed Description

template<typename PTYPE>
class muscle::ConduitExitSingle< PTYPE >

complementary class for the Java muscle.core.JNIConduitExit using single primitive type data, e.g.

muscle.core.JNIConduitExit<java.lang.Double, Object>
use muscle::ConduitExitArray to access arrays of primitive data instead of single values
note: though java.lang.Double is an object, the muscle::ConduitExitSingle will yield a jdouble, not a jobject access an exit which yields single primitive datatypes (receive)

Jan Hegewald
